From Subject Re Real Time Graphics In article Jim Stockel writes Hi I will be writing a data acquisition program to collect data from a variety of sources including and external A D's and I would like to be able to display the data in near I've done this type of thing on PC's and other machines but I am unaware of any graphics package that could help me with this on a UNIX Does anyone have any ideas on commercial or free packages that might suit my needs I would really appreciate any I'm sure this has been done many times For a commerical package try WAVE from Precision Visuals For a free package try KHOROS from University of New Mexico ftp from Login in anonyomus or ftp with a valid email address as the password cd pub khoros release That will get you to the right David